President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 11, 2014, as Mother's Day in the United States. The proclamation acknowledges the important role that mothers play in society and highlights the achievements and contributions of women. It also recognizes the ongoing challenges faced by working mothers, such as the gender pay gap, and emphasizes the importance of supporting mothers in achieving their dreams. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to express love and gratitude to mothers and to observe the day with appropriate programs and activities.